messages.msgSnippet: The cameras were rolling when a mini bus pulled up in front of a local Winn Dixie Supermarket. This was to me, the most shocking 60 minutes ever aired on TV!
messages.messageBody:
The cameras were rolling when a mini bus pulled up in front of a
local Winn Dixie Supermarket. This was to me, the most shocking 60
minutes ever aired on TV! About 20 people got off the bus and the
cameras followed these people throughout the store. Each person
systematcally filled their carts with everything you could imagine,
groceries, film, pet needs, baby goods, cleaners, toiletries, etc.
Then one by one they went to the cashier and had their orders rung
up. The smallest order was in the neighborhood of $600.00. They are
all members of a program at: http://www.wrldofproducts.com One by one
they presented the coupons that they receive from this program and
the deducutions began. The most anyone had to pay was $19.66 and even
that person had an overflowing cart! I joined this program minutes
after the show aired and I still can't believe my eyes when week
after week I leave the supermarket with a full cart of products for
next to nothing!

PS: Here is the link to their family network of sites:
http://www.networkofsavings.com
